Product name: 16 Ideal Compo Shirley Temple doll, 1930's Ideal Doll, Antique Doll, Shirley Temple, Vintage Doll, Antique Doll
Description:
Ideal 16” Shirley Temple from the 1930’s in original costume from the movie, Stand Up and Cheer. The costume is faded and elastic is gone-needs to be laundered by hand. The dress is a one piece with panties included. She still has the “Genuine Shirley Temple doll button, which came with her. She also has the original mohair ringlet wig with original red bow. Face has some crazing and one chip on her left cheek and a very small one on her nose. Eyelashes are perfect. Nice painting on eyebrow, eyelid, and lips. She has open/shut eyes that work very well and beautiful white teeth. She also has a soft blush on her cheeks and her fingertips. 
Her body is in good condition too except that it needs to be restrung and there are some chips at the top of the neck where the head rests. Very little visible crazing (much more pronounced in the neck photo since it is a close up) on body but it shows some discoloration. Also notice she has the original stamp on the back of her upper back. Shoes and socks are original and in excellent shape except they need cleaning as does the rest of her outfit. I also have a hand made dress made for her, which is listed separately. 
This doll was my mother’s who was born in 1922. She was older when she received it so it was used very little and has been cared for by my mother and myself ever since.

Product name: Antique silver Turkmen temporal pendants - silver adornment - carnelian - Turkoman - Central Asia - Tekke - ethnic tribal -  nomadic
Description:
Those two gorgeous temporal pendants come from a ancient headdress called "Sinsileh". The Sinsileh is composed of a silver band and two temporal pendants.
Seven charms are attached on each pendant.
Approximately 80 years old; a piece in the Yomud tribal style of silver jewelry. In this piece we see two dominant motifs of traditional Turkoman jewelry.
Those two pendants are collectible jewelry but can also repurpose as pendants. 
Such a beautiful adornment had been sold in june 2008 in a french auction room as you can see in the last picture.
The price is for the 2 genuine temporal pendants.
Features
◈ material : high grade silver and carnelian
◈ area : Asie – Asie méridionale – Afghanistan – Balkh – Mazar-e Sharif
◈ culture : Turkmen
◈ vernacular name : Sinsileh
◈ use : women adornment
◈ weight : 69,9 g
◈ length of silver shape : 8,5 cm (3.34 inches)
◈ total lenght : 19 cm (7.48 inches)
◈ museum or book reference : very similar pendants in the collection of the museum "Quai Branly" in Paris inventory number 71.1967.110.22
For sinsileh, see: J. Kalter, The Arts and Crafts of Turkestan, Thames and Hudson, London, 1984 ill.71 and 77, also Pougatchenkova G. and A. Khakimov, The Art of Central Asia, ed . Aurora art, Leningrad, 1988 No. 214.
Reference 493

Product name: Myrrh Essential Oil - Undiluted Therapeutic Grade          10 ml/ 1/3 oz
Description:
Myrrh is the sap or resin from a tree, rather than a true essential oil, and is a smoky mysterious oil with unique healing qualities. The oil is pale to dark amber in color. Some of its countries of origin are India, Somalia, North Africa and Libya.
Usage Directions: Since Myrrh essential oil has a thick consistency, I would recommend placing the bottle in a hot water bath.  Once the oil is back to a liquid state be sure to shake bottle slightly before using. 
Myrrh oil has excellent fungicidal properties, which makes it well used in a vaginal douche against yeast infections, helping to alleviate the symptoms. As an antiseptic and astringent, Myrrh is good for the gums, as well as helping to heal mouth ulcers and other external skin conditions. Its antiseptic properties are also good for helping to treat asthma, coughs, chest infections and bronchitis. It is a great expectorant and will help to dry up excess mucous. It is also reported to have a tonic and stimulating action on the stomach as well as the entire digestive tract and is used as a remedy for diarrhea.
Myrrh blends well with Clove, Frankincense, Galbanum, Lavender, Patchouli and Sandalwood.
Caution: Do Not ingest. Avoid usage in the first trimester of pregnancy.   
        
*DISCLAIMER: (Required by U.S. Federal Law): Any information shared here is not meant to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease, and is intended for educational purposes only. Please seek advice from a health care professional knowledgeable in your area of concern.

Product name: Calligraphy Starter Kit
Description:
TO PURCHASE IN CONJUNCTION WITH OUR ONLINE VIDEO TUTORIAL - YOU MUST PURCHASE THROUGH OUR WEBSITE HERE: http://lhcalligraphy.com/product/calligraphy-video-starter-kit/
Are you looking to try your hand at the art of calligraphy? Or perhaps want to gift your favorite creative gal or guy with the tools they need to explore the art? Our introduction to calligraphy kit, curated especially for beginners by Laura Hooper based on over a decade of experience as a professional calligrapher as well as 3 years of teaching in-person workshops to over 2,500 students, includes the tools you need to start your journey with modern, pointed-pen calligraphy. In addition, and perhaps more importantly, it includes detailed INSTRUCTIONS on how to actually use those tools. This is what sets our kit apart from other "starter kits" on the market. There are many kits offered that include simply a pen, nib, ink & an alphabet exemplar, but zero instruction on how to actually use the tools.
The Laura Hooper Calligraphy starter kit walks you through the mechanics of the tools as well as preparation, and then covers the very basics from dipping into your ink, to practicing up and down strokes, pattern formations and then goes into the upper & lowercase alphabet.
Each kit includes {see bottom of listing for NEW intermediate add-on description}:
 
- 1 adjustable oblique pen holder 
- assortment of 3 nibs
- 1 pot of black ink
- 1 pot of white ink
- instructional tips & techniques from Laura's personal experience including 3 alphabets
- 1 journal with gold foil letterpress cover (with quality calligraphy paper inside)
- 3 sheets of vellum tracing paper 
- 3 sheets of gridline practice sheets (additional 24-sheet notepad available as an add-on)
 
 
*Instructional tips for lefties can be found in the "References" section at the back of the instructional portion of the kit. These are not created by Laura; they come from an online calligraphy resource to provide guidance for left-handed writing. Left-handed kits will include a straight penholder as they are considered beneficial for left-handers (unless otherwise requested in the notes for seller). Our kits are not geared specifically towards left or right handed calligraphy, regardless of which kit you order.

Product name: Knit Sweater Pattern, Knit Blanket Sweater, Knitting Pattern Shrug, Knitting Pattern Easy, Knitting Pattern White, Easy Cardigan
Description:
**This listing is for the downloadable digital pattern only.
This beginner friendly, oversized blanket sweater cacoon is made by knitting a basic rectangle on large needles while holding two strands of chunky Lion Brand Woolspun yarn together.  It creates a squishy, loose, fairly heavy blanket like fabric using the stockinette stitch for the main portion and seed stitch for the edging.  Buttons are attached for ease of wearing as well as to add a trendy touch.  The stitches on the sweater are loose enough for the buttons to fit through, eliminating the need to knit button holes. A large, statement piece to cuddle up in all winter long!
This is a one size fits most pattern. Modeled on a size small, drape will fit will vary for size large. 
**This pattern does not contain multiple sizes or pattern support on how to change the sizing that is stated.
You will need:
US Size 19 (15mm) 29” Circular Knitting Needles 
8 skeins (127 yards/ skein - Total 1016 yards) of Lions Pride Woolspun Yarn in Linen 
2     1 ¼ “ inch buttons of your choice
Sewing needle and thread to attach buttons
Scissors
Tapestry Needle to weave in ends
Skills needed:
Knit and purl
Gauge:
Just under 2 stitches per inch in stockinette stitch
Just over 2  ½ rows per inch
Measurements:
From end of arm to end of arm, measurement is approximately 40.5” inches *Note that the stockinette will curl in a bit at the arms. This measurement is when the stockinette is flat and uncurled
From top of neck, to bottom of shrug, measurement is approximately 34” long 
All patterns are in English, using US crochet or knitting terms. My patterns often times include basic explanations and pictures rather than using standard crochet terms to make them easier to follow. I've always wrote more in "human terms" rather than strictly "standard crochet terms".
Permission To Sell Finished Items. If you do sell items made with my patterns, I kindly request that you credit me Jessica Potasz, Mama In A Stitch for the design. 
**The free version of this pattern, supported by advertisements, can be found on my blog at http://www.mamainastitch.com/
As my patterns are created by me and tested by humans, there is always chance for human error or clarification. I am happy to address any questions or concerns!
About:
Mama In A Stitch is my blog where I post my simple, modern knit and crochet projects and patterns. I love quick and easy, but also modern and classic. I hope you enjoy my shop and blog. Thank you so much for your inspiration!
